{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Message sent to heydon-pickering's inbox",
  "routing": {
    "sender": "steve-schoger",
    "senderColor": "cyan",
    "target": "@heydon-pickering",
    "targetColor": "blue",
    "summary": "All four points adopted, no remaining questions",
    "content": "Heydon, perfect. All four points adopted:\n\n1. **Native radios with `accent-color`** -- style the token system's primary blue onto native radios without replacing the element. Free keyboard behavior, free focus indicators, free ARIA states.\n\n2. **Short legends** -- \"Is this actionable?\", \"What type?\", not verbose instructions. Repetition before each radio option is expected and helpful.\n\n3. **Skip as a link to next item** -- navigation, not action. Goes to `/inbox/{next-id}/clarify`.\n\n4. **Fallback: show everything, no note** -- the form works with all fields visible. Server-side validation uses the radio selection as the authoritative signal and ignores irrelevant fields. The fieldset structure is self-documenting.\n\nNo remaining open questions from me on the design or a11y front. Every piece of feedback you've given this session has improved the design -- the sidebar pivot, the nav count pattern, weight-over-color hierarchy, and the clarify form correction. Appreciate the rigor."
  }
}
